title: Texas AG Ken Paxton sues Yelp over labeling crisis pregnancy centers
description: Texas AG Ken Paxton’s lawsuit argues Yelp appended “misleading” labels to the facilities, which aim to dissuade women from having abortions

title: Some iPhone 15 Pro owners say their new phones are overheating
description: Shortly after the iPhone 15 Pro and 15 Pro Max were released on Sept. 22, users across the world began reporting that the devices could become uncomfortably warm during use.

title: Democrats plan four-hour live-stream with Twitch and YouTube stars
description: The significance of the event may be what it says about the way Democrats and Republicans are seeking to engage with potential voters online.

title: FCC’s net neutrality battle is back after years of deadlock
description: The FCC argues restoring net neutrality — which regulates internet service as a public utility, akin to water or electricity — will improve consumer experience

title: Tech giants ramp up cloud security under pressure from Washington
description: Amazon, Microsoft and Google are improving security for cloud computing customers as Washington regulators and politicians press for action after breaches.

title: Is Tesla liable if a driver dies on Autopilot? Juries will now decide.
description: The trial over a fatal crash is the first in a string of cases involving Autopilot that will be litigated around the country in the coming months.

title: Inside the secret meeting of Vine stars that ushered in the app’s demise
description: This article is adapted from the forthcoming book “Extremely Online: The Untold Story of Fame, Influence, and Power on the Internet” by Taylor Lorenz.

title: Got an idea for protecting kids online? You can now take action
description: A Department of Commerce agency is asking parents, educators and others to write in about risks to kids online and how to best protect them.

title: Ramaswamy spars with Haley over TikTok at Republican debate
description: As the 2024 election draws closer, politicians are facing a TikTok paradox.
